The way I see it there are 4 elements in the trailer, air, water, earth and fire.
Earth can also be branched with plant/wood, seeing that there are grass and plants growing on the earth Elementals. So it is possible that, correction the mother, would pull away her child so he doesn't get burnt by Ember's fire.

@girlgamer6678 Zootopia felt a lot more creative to me. The name was a little bit more than just "animal city" or something, and the name in fact was going off of "zoo utopia" - and the irony in that the city really wasn't that in reality.

I feel like that film had a bit of a hamfisted moral, but its worldbuilding was just really creative. They had the whole animal kingdom to work with and imagine how these animals would interact in modern society. There's also the whole way that we perceive different kinds of animals that they could work with in constructing characters.

This is just... you got the four classical elements. It just sounds... really limiting, very boring.
